🛢️ Create Amazon Aurora MySQL Database
        Step 1 — Navigate to RDS & Start Creation
        Go to AWS Console → Search RDS → Click RDS
        In the left panel, click Databases
        Click Create database
Step 2 — Choose Creation Method
        Select Standard create
        ✅ This enables Full Configuration mode — exposing all available settings

Step 3 — Select Engine Type
      Engine type → Amazon Aurora
      Edition → Amazon Aurora MySQL-Compatible Edition
Step 4 — Choose Template
      Templates → Select Production
Step 5 — Cluster Scalability Type
      Cluster scalability type → Provisioned
Step 6 — Instance Configuration (Burstable Classes)
      DB instance class → Select Burstable classes (includes t classes)
      Choose an instance size, e.g. db.t3.medium or db.t4g.medium
Step 7 — Set DB Cluster Identifier
        DB cluster identifier → database-2
Step 8 — Configure Credentials (Self Managed)
        Master username → admin(default)
        Credentials management → Self managed
        Master password → admin123
        Confirm password → admin123
Step 9 — Connectivity & VPC Security Group
        Scroll down to Connectivity
        Under VPC security group (firewall) → Choose Select existing
        Remove the default SG (if any) → Select demo-sg-rds-aurora
Step 10 — Additional Configuration
      Scroll down → Expand Additional configuration
      Under Database options:
      Initial database name → myDb
        💡 If left blank, no default database is created — you'd have to create it manually via MySQL client.
Step 11 — Create the Database
      Review all settings
      Scroll to the bottom → Click Create database
      Status will show Creating → changes to Available in approximately 5–15 minutes
